      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level. Required level 3: model form assumptions documented and justified with supporting literature or sensitivity analysis.",
      "rationale": "Linear elastic titanium alloy (Ti-6Al-4V) with bilinear isotropic hardening for post-yield behavior. Contact modeled with augmented Lagrangian formulation. Cortical and cancellous bone substitute (UHMWPE blocks per ASTM F1717) represented as elastic-perfectly-plastic. Model form assumptions justified by published material characterization data and sensitivity analysis showing <3% QoI sensitivity to ±10% modulus variation. Achieved level 3 meets required level 3."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level. Required level 3: material properties and geometric inputs traceable to measurements with uncertainty quantification.",
      "rationale": "Geometric inputs derived from CMM measurements of production screws (n=5) with dimensional tolerances applied. Material properties sourced from certificate of conformance and literature (ASTM B265 Ti-6Al-4V). UHMWPE block properties from tensile coupon testing (n=6 per lot). Uncertainty in inputs propagated via Latin Hypercube sampling (500 runs). Achieved level 3 meets required level 3."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level. Required level 3: test samples traceable to production lots with documented dimensional and material characterization.",
      "rationale": "N=11 constructs assembled from production-representative 7.5 mm non-cannulated pedicle screws (two lots, lot numbers recorded). Screw dimensions verified by CMM; UHMWPE blocks from single certified lot. Sample preparation per ASTM F1717 Section 7. Achieved level 3 meets required level 3."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level. Required level 3: multiple test conditions spanning the COU envelope exercised. Achieved level 2 is below required level — single test condition (ASTM F1717 standard geometry only) was tested.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed at a single standardized test condition (ASTM F1717 standard 44 mm inter-body distance, room temperature, displacement-controlled at 5 mm/min) across two independent laboratories. No variation in test geometry, temperature, or loading rate was evaluated. This represents a gap relative to the required level 3; the shortfall is accepted given that the ASTM F1717 condition is the regulatory submission standard and model predictions are not extrapolated beyond this condition. Achieved level 2 is below required level 3 — documented gap."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level. Required level 3: model inputs set to match measured test specimen properties with documented traceability.",
      "rationale": "FEA model inputs set to match measured specimen geometry (CMM) and material properties (CoC + coupon testing) for each of the 11 constructs. Torque-to-angle data from screw insertion used to set initial preload state in model. Input equivalency matrix documented with traceability to test records. Achieved level 3 meets required level 3."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level. Required level 3: quantitative comparison metric with uncertainty (E/uval) reported against pre-defined acceptance bounds.",
      "rationale": "Quantitative comparison performed using the ASME V&V 40 validation metric E/uval. Experimental uncertainty uval estimated from inter-laboratory reproducibility (two labs, n=11 total). E/uval = 0.87 (stiffness), 1.42 (yield force), 1.61 (force at 40 mm) — all below the 1.96 threshold. Percent differences all below 10% pre-defined bound. Achieved level 3 meets required level 3."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level. Required level 3: QoIs directly map to clinical and regulatory decision criteria.",
      "rationale": "Three QoIs selected — construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement — directly correspond to ASTM F1717 reported metrics and FDA regulatory submission requirements for spinal implant mechanical performance. Clinical relevance established: yield force predicts onset of permanent deformation under physiologic loading; stiffness predicts load-sharing with bone graft. Achieved level 3 meets required level 3."
    },
    {
